n’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."]}]},{"name":"ap","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Llywelyn ap Iorwerth was born about 1060, in Merionethshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Iorwerth ap Cadwgon, was 31 and his mother, Gwenllian ARON, was 42. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Ellyw verch Elidir."},"et":{"about 1060–":"umbes 1060–Surnud","1040–1124":"1040–1124","1050–Female":"1050–Surnud","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","1100–Female":"1100–Surnud","1105–1164":"1105–1164","–Male":"Surnud","1030–Male":"1030–Surnud","1020–1121":"1020–1121","about 1060":"umbes 1060","1105":"1105","1124":"1124","1100":"1100","1121":"1121","1164":"1164","1020":"1020","1030":"1030","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","1060":"1060","Merionethshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Merionethshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1060–":"noin 1060–Kuollut","1040–1124":"1040–1124","1050–Female":"1050–Kuollut","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","1100–Female":"1100–Kuollut","1105–1164":"1105–1164","–Male":"Kuollut","1030–Male":"1030–Kuollut","1020–1121":"1020–1121","about 1060":"noin 1060","1105":"1105","1124":"1124","1100":"1100","1121":"1121","1164":"1164","1020":"1020","1030":"1030","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","1060":"1060","Merionethshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Merionethshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1060–":"envi